  <h2>Permitting in Hillsborough (and the City of Tampa is different)</h2>
  <p>Hillsborough County and the City of Tampa have separate permitting tracks. Unincorporated Hillsborough — Brandon, Riverview, FishHawk, Valrico, Carrollwood, Westchase — goes through Hillsborough County Building & Construction Services. Homes inside Tampa city limits (South Tampa, Hyde Park, Seminole Heights, Ybor, New Tampa) use the City of Tampa Construction Services office. We handle both, daily, and we know exactly which affidavits are required for homes built before specific code cycles (a common FishHawk issue).</p>

  <h2>Coastal &amp; flood-prone Tampa installs</h2>
  <p>Homes in South Tampa (Bayshore, Davis Islands, Harbour Island) and along the Tampa Bay waterfront are routinely in FEMA AE flood zones. We elevate condensers on engineered stands, spec stainless hardware, route line sets above flood elevations, and install surge-protected disconnects. Post-Hurricane Idalia and Hurricane Helene we replaced hundreds of coastal outdoor units in Hillsborough — that's specialty work most franchises get wrong.</p>

  <h2>Carrollwood, Westchase, FishHawk &amp; Tampa Palms HOA compliance</h2>
  <p>The bigger master-planned HOAs have detailed condenser rules: max dB ratings, visual-screen requirements, approved pad materials, neighbor-side offset distances. We bring the spec sheet. For Carrollwood Village, Westchase, FishHawk Ranch, Tampa Palms, Cross Creek and Cory Lake Isles, we already have the HOA approval template; we complete it with your install and submit it in your name — one less thing on your list.</p>

